===Etymology===
Via {{etyl|enm|en}} and {{etyl|fro|en}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|perdīx||partridge|lang=la}}, from {{etyl|grc|en}} {{term|πέρδιξ||partridge|lang=grc}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ˈpɑːtrɪd͡ʒ/|lang=en}}
* {{a|US}} {{enPR|pärʹtrĭj}}, {{IPA|/ˈpɑrtrɪd͡ʒ/|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun|s|partridge}}

# Any [[bird]] of a number of [[genera]] in the family ''[[Phasianidae]]'', notably in the genera ''[[Perdix]]'' and ''[[Alectoris]]''.
# {{context|obsolete|military|lang=en}} A type cannon charge composed of several missiles fired all together, similar to [[langrage]] or [[case-shot]]. Also a large cannon that shoots stones.

